    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-10T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.00/10–1048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baruch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-10T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 10, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 10—11:17 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>684. Have seen Foreign Minister as per instruction first paragraph <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 503, October 9, and reiterated our
                    government’s position as set forth in appropriate paragraph pouched to us of
                    Under Secretary’s conversation with Stikker.<note n="1" xml:id="d313fn1"
                        >September 17, <ref target="#pg_345">p. 345</ref>.</note> Foreign Minister
                    had not clearly recalled latter part of Under Secretary’s remarks concerning
                    possible agreement on elections. He expressed much satisfaction, and I believe
                    atmosphere clearing here and with Schuurman.</p>
                <p>We have strongly and continuously in accordance with Department’s guidance and
                    Cochran’s suggestion attempted to break down stubborn insistence of Foreign
                    Minister that Netherlands plan be presented <pb facs="0415" n="401"
                        xml:id="pg_401"/> to Republican representatives advance of <gloss
                        target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> meeting to discuss Cochran’s plan. We have
                    repeatedly told Foreign Minister that the Dutch are putting too much emphasis on
                    procedure and that this must not be permitted to balk this urgent business.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 684; Department pass Batavia.<note n="2" xml:id="d313fn2">This
                        was done the same day.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baruch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
